snippet.title: Song of the Welkin Moon Teaser: Moonlit Ballad of the Night | Genshin Impact #GenshinImpact
snippet.description:
She scatters dewdrops upon every bloom,
And tints the twilight with a sheen of silver.

Thus do shadows howl across the gloomy woods,
As flocks of deer and birds take fright and shiver.

She hums one nameless tune,
While walking through those solitary halls.

So her homeland may not fall to desolation,
So the tale may not be lost to oblivion.

localized.title: Song of the Welkin Moon Teaser: Moonlit Ballad of the Night | Genshin Impact #GenshinImpact
localized.description:
She scatters dewdrops upon every bloom,
And tints the twilight with a sheen of silver.

Thus do shadows howl across the gloomy woods,
As flocks of deer and birds take fright and shiver.

She hums one nameless tune,
While walking through those solitary halls.

So her homeland may not fall to desolation,
So the tale may not be lost to oblivion.

en.description:
She scatters dewdrops upon every bloom,
And tints the twilight with a sheen of silver.

Thus do shadows howl across the gloomy woods,
As flocks of deer and birds take fright and shiver.

She hums one nameless tune,
While walking through those solitary halls.

So her homeland may not fall to desolation,
So the tale may not be lost to oblivion.

snippet.title: Bill Cosby breaks silence following death of co-star Malcolm-Jamal Warner
snippet.description:
Malcolm-Jamal Warner, the actor perhaps best known for starring in the TV sitcom "The Cosby Show" as son Theodore "Theo" Huxtable, has died at 54.

Warner drowned off the coast of Costa Rica on Sunday, Costa Rican National Police told ABC News. Warner's official cause of death was asphyxia, police said.

In an interview with 6abc, Bill Cosby, who is a native of Montgomery County, Pennsylvania, spoke about Jamal Warner's death.

"You could depend on Malcolm always going to uh the shelter, to learn his lines, to gather his character to come out and be ready. When the news came, it was shocking. And of course, my thoughts went straight to his mother, who worked so hard. She was so wonderful with him," Cosby told 6abc anchor Sharrie Williams.
#billcosby #news #fyp #fypage

snippet.title: Brittany Force makes the fastest run in NHRA history
snippet.description:
The first matchup of 340-plus-mph dragsters didn't disappoint as Brittany Force not only defeated Doug Kalitta but did it with the fastest speed ever, a national-record 341.85 mph on a 3.659 pass. Her run is quicker than her Funny Car teammate Austin Prock's 341.68 from last year's season finale. This event has now been host to four of the six fastest speeds in Top Fuel history. 


This is a @FendtTV record-setting performance.

id.title: Brittany Force mencatatkan rekor lari tercepat dalam sejarah NHRA
id.description:

Plus former two-division world champion Brandon ‚ÄúThe Heartbreaker‚Äù Figueroa and top contender Joet Gonzalez kick off the pay-per-view at 8 p.m. ET/5 p.m. PT with a 10-round featherweight showdown.

snippet.title: Highlights: Liverpool 5-0 Stoke | Darwin Nunez Hat-trick, Chiesa & Ngumoha Goals
snippet.description:
Watch highlights from the AXA Training Centre as Liverpool hosted Stoke City in a behind-closed doors pre-season friendly. Darwin Nunez netted three times inside the opening 20 minutes of the contest, with Rio Ngumoha and Federico Chiesa addding their names to the scoresheet either side of half-time, as the Reds made it two wins from two this summer prior to flying out for their tour to Asia.

Liverpool first-half team: Mamardashvili, Gomez, Van Dijk, Szoboszlai, Nunez, Salah, Jones, Robertson, Wirtz, Ngumoha, Nyoni.

Liverpool second-half team: Mamardashvili (Pecsi, 59), Endo, Konate, Chiesa, Gakpo, Tsimikas, Gravenberch, Doak (Stephenson, 74), Kerkez, Frimpong, Bradley.

snippet.title: Woman Who Shot Coldplay Kisscam Speaks Out
snippet.description: The woman who shot that Coldplay kisscam that caught a pair of executives in a private moment is speaking out to Inside Edition. Grace Springer captured the moment Andy Byron, CEO of billion-dollar A.I. company Astronomer, and Kristin Cabot, the company's head of human resources, were seen shrinking in panic from a cozy clinch at the concert in Boston. Fortune magazine is predicting "severe consequences for the company's culture, reputation, and financial stability."

snippet.title: Mumbo Update 2025
snippet.description:
Today I give you all an update on what's going with me in 2025, 3 years after leaving YouTube. I talk about Hermitcraft Season 10, my plans for Hermitcraft Season 11, retiring from YouTube and my struggles with disordered eating. 

I am not a professional; I would highly recommend seeking professional advice from therapists specialising in disordered eating if this is something you‚Äôre deeply struggling with.

My first piece of advice is to look at lifestyle transformation over a macro time scale as opposed to focusing on quick fixes. I would put myself on these unsustainable restrictive diets, tell myself I needed to exercise at an incredible intensity almost daily, and within a week I be would exhausted, unmotivated and inevitably fall off the wagon - I would then beat myself up for ‚Äòfailing again‚Äô and comfort myself by bingeing heavily. 

One thing that really helped me is getting 3-4 incredibly quick recipes that I can cook. I‚Äôm talking less than 5 minutes. Are they the absolute healthiest wholefood gold standard? No. But a perfect gold standard recipe that takes a trip to the shop and 30 minutes to prepare actually means I‚Äôm eating a triple cheese blend pizza hut for dinner as soon as I‚Äôm under any time pressure.

Some examples of these hyper fast meals:

- Microwave burrito bean mix rice, Microwave chill non-carne, Tofu, tenderstem brocolli, some feta cheese. All chucked in a single pan. Over 80g of protein, loads of fibre. 5 minutes max.
- A cold pasta pot (tomato and herb), tofu, feta cheese. All in one pan literally just to heat it, maybe 3 minutes? I will also mix up the pasta pots for pesto/chilli ones for variety.
- Stir fry mix. Some kind of noodle packet with flavouring provided, a stirfry veg mix, tofu. Maybe 5 minutes?
- Falaffels and couscous, maybe some humous and pita breads.

Again, are they perfect? No. But you have to think of the reality. You can write out the perfect plan with macro calories calculated to the second decimal place, a huge veg variety, and 12 hours of exercise mapped to all the different muscle groups, but a plan is just a plan, it doesn‚Äôt exist. The real story is how you interact with it, and if you can‚Äôt sustain your plan for more than 3 days it‚Äôs not really a plan at all. These meals are delicious, easy, satiating, cheap, available from basically any shop, last for days in the fridge, and take less time than ordering takeaways. Having these burden free options mean you are likely to integrate them into a sustainable lifestyle change, as opposed to hunting for absolute perfection.

On that note; a lot of people with disordered eating listen to health and wellness podcasts. I would possibly recommend stopping that, they tend to fear monger and hyperbolise the negative effects of relatively innocuous foods. This again can lead to catastrophizing the tiniest of ‚Äòimperfections‚Äô such as eating an ‚Äòultra processed protein bar‚Äô or drinking a sugar free soda. I switched out my ‚Äòhealth‚Äô podcasts for ones that focus on hobbies I enjoy, and that was far better.

I got rid of my scale, I haven‚Äôt weighed myself in about a year. Your weight fluctuates a lot daily, and those swings I really struggled with. If I was heavily restricting and woke up heavier I would immediately give up. I would also restrict super hard excited by how much I could lose in a day. Getting rid immediately switched my mentality from thinking on a daily timescale to a long term one. I do take ‚Äòprogress‚Äô photos every now again, and my health metrics are tracked by my apple watch, but I don‚Äôt really put much effort into any measurements. 

In terms of activity, my lifestyle shift happened over 3 years: I began indoor climbing 1-2 times a week, I then slowly built a friend group around climbing who I love spending time with, my love for indoor climbing then spread to a love for outdoor climbing, which then meant I started training for hiking, which gave me the fitness to pursue alpine climbing. I prioritise these hobbies and do them whenever I get any free time, because I love them and my life is built around them. Instead of going for food/drinking with friends we go climbing. If we all get a free day, we go hiking. If we sync up weeks off we go on a trip to the mountains. I know most people have less flexible schedules than me, and kids etc. massively complicate things, but if you can find a form of exercise that you truly love, be it BJJ, running, roller derby, skateboarding, surfing, yoga etc. and build your social structure around it, things will fall into place. To put it simply, I don‚Äôt think of anything I do as ‚Äòexercise‚Äô I just view it as fun, in the same way a kid doesn‚Äôt view running everywhere and playing tag as a workout!

But as I say - this is all a process. Having spent a full day editing this and hearing myself talk about food the whole time, I ordered a pizza lol

id.title: Pembaruan Mumbo 2025
id.description:
Hari ini saya akan memberi Anda semua kabar terbaru tentang apa yang akan terjadi pada saya di tahun 2025, 3 tahun setelah meninggalkan YouTube. Saya akan membahas Hermitcraft Musim 10, rencana saya untuk Hermitcraft Musim 11, pensiun dari YouTube, dan perjuangan saya melawan gangguan makan.

Saya bukan seorang profesional; saya sangat menyarankan untuk mencari nasihat profesional dari terapis yang berspesialisasi dalam gangguan makan jika ini adalah sesuatu yang sangat Anda perjuangkan.

Saran pertama saya adalah untuk melihat transformasi gaya hidup dalam skala waktu makro, alih-alih berfokus pada solusi cepat. Saya akan memaksakan diri untuk menjalani diet ketat yang tidak berkelanjutan, meyakinkan diri sendiri bahwa saya perlu berolahraga dengan intensitas yang luar biasa hampir setiap hari, dan dalam seminggu saya akan kelelahan, kehilangan motivasi, dan akhirnya menyerah ‚Äì saya kemudian akan menyalahkan diri sendiri karena 'gagal lagi' dan menghibur diri dengan makan berlebihan.

Satu hal yang sangat membantu saya adalah mendapatkan 3-4 resep cepat yang bisa saya masak. Maksud saya kurang dari 5 menit. Apakah itu standar emas makanan utuh yang paling sehat? Tidak. Tapi resep standar emas sempurna yang hanya butuh waktu 30 menit untuk pergi ke toko, artinya saya bisa langsung makan Pizza Hut dengan campuran tiga keju untuk makan malam begitu saya merasa tertekan.

Beberapa contoh makanan super cepat ini:

- Nasi campur kacang burrito microwave, nasi non-carne dingin microwave, tahu, brokoli tenderstem, sedikit keju feta. Semua diolah dalam satu loyang. Lebih dari 80g protein, kaya serat. Maksimal 5 menit.
- Panci pasta dingin (tomat dan herba), tahu, keju feta. Semua diolah dalam satu loyang, hanya untuk memanaskannya saja, mungkin 3 menit? Saya juga akan mencampur panci pasta dengan pesto/cabai untuk variasi.
- Campuran tumis. Semacam bungkus mi dengan bumbu yang disediakan, campuran sayuran tumis, tahu. Mungkin 5 menit?
- Falaffel dan kuskus, mungkin hummus dan roti pita.

Sekali lagi, apakah semuanya sempurna? Tidak. Tapi Anda harus memikirkan realitanya. Anda bisa saja menulis rencana yang sempurna dengan kalori makro yang dihitung hingga desimal kedua, variasi sayuran yang melimpah, dan 12 jam latihan yang dipetakan ke semua kelompok otot yang berbeda, tetapi rencana hanyalah rencana, tidak ada. Kisah sebenarnya adalah bagaimana Anda berinteraksi dengannya, dan jika Anda tidak dapat mempertahankan rencana Anda selama lebih dari 3 hari, itu bukanlah rencana sama sekali. Makanan-makanan ini lezat, mudah, mengenyangkan, murah, tersedia di hampir semua toko, tahan berhari-hari di lemari es, dan membutuhkan waktu lebih singkat daripada memesan makanan untuk dibawa pulang. Memiliki pilihan-pilihan bebas beban ini berarti Anda cenderung mengintegrasikannya ke dalam perubahan gaya hidup yang berkelanjutan, alih-alih mengejar kesempurnaan mutlak.

Terkait hal itu; banyak orang dengan gangguan makan mendengarkan podcast kesehatan dan kebugaran. Saya mungkin menyarankan untuk menghentikannya, mereka cenderung menakut-nakuti dan melebih-lebihkan efek negatif dari makanan yang relatif tidak berbahaya. Hal ini lagi-lagi bisa membuat saya membesar-besarkan 'ketidaksempurnaan' sekecil apa pun, seperti makan 'protein bar ultra-olahan' atau minum soda bebas gula. Saya mengganti podcast 'kesehatan' saya dengan podcast yang berfokus pada hobi yang saya sukai, dan itu jauh lebih baik.

Saya menyingkirkan timbangan, saya belum menimbang berat badan selama kurang lebih setahun. Berat badan kita berfluktuasi sangat banyak setiap hari, dan fluktuasi itu sangat sulit saya hadapi. Jika saya sangat membatasi diri dan bangun tidur dengan berat badan lebih, saya akan langsung menyerah. Saya juga akan membatasi diri dengan sangat bersemangat tentang berapa banyak yang bisa saya turunkan dalam sehari. Menyingkirkan timbangan langsung mengubah pola pikir saya dari berpikir berdasarkan jangka waktu harian menjadi jangka panjang. Saya memang mengambil foto 'kemajuan' sesekali, dan metrik kesehatan saya dilacak oleh Apple Watch saya, tetapi saya tidak terlalu berusaha melakukan pengukuran apa pun.

Dalam hal aktivitas, perubahan gaya hidup saya terjadi selama 3 tahun: Saya mulai memanjat dalam ruangan 1-2 kali seminggu, kemudian saya perlahan-lahan membangun kelompok teman di sekitar pendakian yang saya senangi untuk menghabiskan waktu bersama, kecintaan saya untuk memanjat dalam ruangan kemudian menyebar ke kecintaan untuk memanjat luar ruangan, yang kemudian berarti saya mulai berlatih hiking, yang memberi saya kebugaran untuk menekuni pendakian alpine. Saya memprioritaskan hobi-hobi ini dan melakukannya kapan pun saya punya waktu luang, karena saya menyukainya dan hidup saya dibangun di sekitarnya. Alih-alih pergi makan/minum dengan teman-teman, kami pergi memanjat. Jika kami semua mendapat hari libur, kami pergi hiking. Jika kami menyinkronkan minggu libur, kami pergi bertamasya ke pegunungan. Saya tahu kebanyakan orang memil...

nl-NL.title: Mumbo Update 2025
nl-NL.description:
Vandaag geef ik jullie een update over hoe het met me gaat in 2025, 3 jaar nadat ik YouTube heb verlaten. Ik praat over Hermitcraft seizoen 10, mijn plannen voor Hermitcraft seizoen 11, stoppen met YouTube en mijn worsteling met een eetstoornis.

Ik ben geen professional; ik raad je ten zeerste aan om professioneel advies te zoeken bij therapeuten die gespecialiseerd zijn in eetstoornissen als je hier echt mee worstelt.

Mijn eerste advies is om je levensstijlverandering te bekijken op een macroschaal in plaats van je te richten op snelle oplossingen. Ik zette mezelf op die onhoudbare, beperkende di√´ten, zei tegen mezelf dat ik bijna dagelijks ongelooflijk intensief moest sporten, en binnen een week was ik uitgeput, ongemotiveerd en viel ik onvermijdelijk terug - dan gaf ik mezelf de schuld omdat ik 'weer faalde' en troostte mezelf met zware eetbuien.

Wat me echt heeft geholpen, is het vinden van 3-4 ongelooflijk snelle recepten die ik kan koken. Ik heb het dan over minder dan 5 minuten. Zijn ze de absoluut gezondste, pure, gouden standaard? Nee. Maar een perfect gouden standaard recept dat een tripje naar de winkel en 30 minuten bereidingstijd kost, betekent dat ik een pizzahut met drie soorten kaas als avondeten eet zodra ik tijdgebrek heb.

Enkele voorbeelden van deze supersnelle maaltijden:

- Rijst van een burrito met bonenmix in de magnetron, non-carne uit de magnetron, tofu, broccoli, wat feta. Alles in √©√©n pan. Meer dan 80 gram eiwit, veel vezels. Maximaal 5 minuten.
- Een pan koude pasta (tomaat en kruiden), tofu, feta. Alles in √©√©n pan, letterlijk alleen om het op te warmen, misschien 3 minuten? Ik ga de pastapotten ook mengen met pesto/chili voor de afwisseling.
- Roerbakmix. Een soort noedelpakket met smaakmakers, een roerbakgroentemix, tofu. Misschien 5 minuten?
- Falafel en couscous, misschien wat hummus en pitabroodjes.

Nogmaals, zijn ze perfect? Nee. Maar je moet de realiteit onder ogen zien. Je kunt het perfecte plan opstellen met macrocalorie√´n tot op de tweede decimaal berekend, een enorme variatie aan groenten en 12 uur beweging voor alle verschillende spiergroepen, maar een plan is slechts een plan, het bestaat niet. Het echte verhaal is hoe je ermee omgaat, en als je je plan niet langer dan 3 dagen kunt volhouden, is het eigenlijk helemaal geen plan. Deze maaltijden zijn heerlijk, makkelijk, vullend, goedkoop, verkrijgbaar in vrijwel elke winkel, dagen houdbaar in de koelkast en kosten minder tijd dan afhaalmaaltijden bestellen. Door deze makkelijke opties te hebben, is de kans groter dat je ze integreert in een duurzame verandering van levensstijl, in plaats van te streven naar absolute perfectie.

Over dat onderwerp gesproken: veel mensen met een eetstoornis luisteren naar podcasts over gezondheid en welzijn. Ik zou aanraden om daarmee te stoppen, ze hebben de neiging om angst te zaaien en de negatieve effecten van relatief onschuldige voedingsmiddelen te overdrijven. Dit kan er weer toe leiden dat de kleinste 'imperfecties', zoals het eten van een 'ultra-processed protein bar' of het drinken van een suikervrije frisdrank, catastrofaal worden. Ik heb mijn 'gezondheids'-podcasts ingeruild voor podcasts die zich richten op hobby's die ik leuk vind, en dat was veel beter.

Ik heb mijn weegschaal weggedaan. Ik heb mezelf ongeveer een jaar niet meer gewogen. Je gewicht schommelt dagelijks enorm, en met die schommelingen had ik echt moeite. Als ik me enorm zou beperken en zwaarder wakker zou worden, zou ik het meteen opgeven. Ik zou me ook enorm beperken, enthousiast over hoeveel ik op een dag zou kunnen afvallen. Door mijn dieet meteen weg te doen, veranderde mijn mentaliteit van denken op een dagelijkse tijdschaal naar denken op de lange termijn. Ik maak wel zo nu en dan 'voortgangs'-foto's en mijn gezondheidsgegevens worden bijgehouden door mijn Apple Watch, maar ik steek er niet echt veel moeite in.

Qua activiteit vond mijn levensstijlverandering plaats in drie jaar tijd: ik begon √©√©n √† twee keer per week indoor te klimmen. Daarna bouwde ik langzaam een vriendengroep op rond klimmen met wie ik graag tijd doorbracht. Mijn liefde voor indoor klimmen verspreidde zich vervolgens naar een liefde voor outdoor klimmen, wat betekende dat ik begon met trainen voor hiken, wat me de conditie gaf om alpinisme te beoefenen. Ik geef prioriteit aan deze hobby's en doe ze wanneer ik tijd heb, omdat ik ze geweldig vind en mijn leven eromheen is gebouwd. In plaats van met vrienden te gaan eten/drinken, gaan we klimmen. Als we allemaal een vrije dag hebben, gaan we hiken. Als we weken vrij hebben, gaan we op reis naar de bergen. Ik weet dat de meeste mensen minder flexibele schema's hebben dan ik, en kinderen en dergelijke maken de dingen enorm ingewikkeld, maar als je een vorm van beweging kunt vinden die je echt leuk vindt, of het nu BJJ, hardlopen, rollerderby, skateboarden, surfen, yoga enz. is, en je sociale structuur eromheen bouwt, dan vallen de dingen op hun plek. Simpel gezegd, ik zie niet...

es-US.title: Actualizaci√≥n de Mumbo 2025
es-US.description:
Hoy les cuento qu√© me espera en 2025, 3 a√±os despu√©s de dejar YouTube. Hablo de la temporada 10 de Hermitcraft, mis planes para la temporada 11 de Hermitcraft, mi retiro de YouTube y mis problemas con los trastornos alimenticios.

No soy profesional; recomiendo encarecidamente buscar asesoramiento profesional de terapeutas especializados en trastornos alimenticios si se trata de algo con lo que est√°s luchando seriamente.

Mi primer consejo es considerar la transformaci√≥n de tu estilo de vida a lo largo del tiempo, en lugar de centrarte en soluciones r√°pidas. Me pon√≠a dietas restrictivas insostenibles, me dec√≠a que necesitaba hacer ejercicio a una intensidad incre√≠ble casi a diario, y en una semana estaba agotada, desmotivada e inevitablemente me sal√≠a del camino. Luego me culpaba por haber "fallado otra vez" y me consolaba con atracones.

Algo que me ayud√≥ mucho fue conseguir 3 o 4 recetas incre√≠blemente r√°pidas que puedo cocinar. Hablo de menos de 5 minutos. ¬øSon la mejor opci√≥n de comida integral y saludable? No. Pero una receta perfecta de primera calidad que requiere ir a la tienda y 30 minutos de preparaci√≥n significa que, en cuanto tengo prisa, me como una Pizza Hut con tres quesos para cenar.

Algunos ejemplos de estas comidas ultrarr√°pidas:

- Burrito de arroz con frijoles, chile sin carne para microondas, tofu, br√≥coli tierno y queso feta. Todo en una sola sart√©n. M√°s de 80 g de prote√≠na y much√≠sima fibra. M√°ximo 5 minutos.
- Una olla de pasta fr√≠a (tomate y hierbas), tofu y queso feta. Todo en una sola sart√©n, literalmente, solo para calentarlo, ¬øquiz√°s 3 minutos? Tambi√©n cambiar√© las ollas de pasta por otras con pesto o chile para variar.
- Mezcla para salteados. Alg√∫n paquete de fideos con saborizante, una mezcla de verduras para saltear y tofu. ¬øQuiz√°s 5 minutos?
- Falaffels y cusc√∫s, quiz√°s un poco de hummus y pan pita.

De nuevo, ¬øson perfectos? No. Pero tienes que pensar en la realidad. Puedes elaborar un plan perfecto con macrocalor√≠as calculadas con precisi√≥n, una gran variedad de verduras y 12 horas de ejercicio dirigidas a todos los grupos musculares, pero un plan es solo un plan, no existe. La clave est√° en c√≥mo interact√∫as con √©l, y si no puedes mantenerlo durante m√°s de 3 d√≠as, no es un plan en absoluto. Estas comidas son deliciosas, f√°ciles, sacian, baratas, se pueden encontrar en pr√°cticamente cualquier tienda, duran d√≠as en la nevera y se hacen en menos tiempo que pedir comida a domicilio. Contar con estas opciones sin complicaciones significa que probablemente las integrar√°s en un cambio de estilo de vida sostenible, en lugar de buscar la perfecci√≥n absoluta.

En ese sentido, muchas personas con trastornos alimentarios escuchan podcasts de salud y bienestar. Quiz√°s recomendar√≠a dejar de hacerlo, ya que tienden a alarmistas e hiperbolizar los efectos negativos de alimentos relativamente inocuos. Esto, de nuevo, puede llevar a catastrofizar las m√°s m√≠nimas imperfecciones, como comer una barra de prote√≠na ultraprocesada o beber un refresco sin az√∫car. Cambi√© mis podcasts de salud por otros centrados en aficiones que disfruto, y eso fue mucho mejor.

Me deshice de la b√°scula; no me he pesado en casi un a√±o. El peso fluct√∫a mucho a diario, y esos cambios me costaron mucho. Si me restring√≠a mucho y me despertaba con m√°s peso, lo dejaba de inmediato. Tambi√©n me restring√≠a much√≠simo, emocionada por lo mucho que pod√≠a perder en un d√≠a. Dejar de pensar inmediatamente cambi√≥ mi mentalidad de pensar en una escala de tiempo diaria a una a largo plazo. De vez en cuando tomo fotos de mi progreso y mi Apple Watch registra mis m√©tricas de salud, pero no le dedico mucho esfuerzo a ninguna medici√≥n.

it.title: Aggiornamento Mumbo 2025
it.description:
Oggi vi aggiorner√≤ su cosa mi aspetta nel 2025, 3 anni dopo aver lasciato YouTube. Parler√≤ della stagione 10 di Hermitcraft, dei miei piani per la stagione 11 di Hermitcraft, del mio ritiro da YouTube e delle mie difficolt√† con i disturbi alimentari.

Non sono una professionista; consiglio vivamente di consultare un terapeuta specializzato in disturbi alimentari se si sta affrontando un problema serio.

Il mio primo consiglio √® di considerare la trasformazione del proprio stile di vita su una scala temporale macro, invece di concentrarsi su soluzioni rapide. Mi sottoporrei a diete restrittive insostenibili, mi direi che dovrei allenarmi a un'intensit√† incredibile quasi ogni giorno, e nel giro di una settimana sarei esausta, demotivata e inevitabilmente perderei il controllo. Poi mi rimprovererei per "aver fallito di nuovo" e mi consolo con abbuffate.

Una cosa che mi ha davvero aiutato √® stata trovare 3-4 ricette incredibilmente veloci da cucinare. Parlo di meno di 5 minuti. Sono il gold standard pi√π sano in assoluto per gli alimenti integrali? No. Ma una ricetta perfetta che richiede un salto al supermercato e 30 minuti di preparazione significa che manger√≤ una pizza tripla di formaggio per cena non appena mi trover√≤ sotto pressione.

Alcuni esempi di questi pasti superveloci:

- Riso con mix di fagioli burrito al microonde, riso freddo senza carne al microonde, tofu, broccoli teneri, un po' di feta. Il tutto in un'unica padella. Oltre 80 g di proteine, un sacco di fibre. Massimo 5 minuti.
- Un pentolino di pasta fredda (pomodoro ed erbe aromatiche), tofu, feta. Tutto in una padella, letteralmente solo per scaldarlo, magari 3 minuti? Misceler√≤ anche i pentolini di pasta con pesto/peperoncino per variare.
- Mix per soffritto. Un pacchetto di noodles con condimento incluso, un mix di verdure per soffritto, tofu. Forse 5 minuti?
- Falaffel e couscous, magari hummus e pita.

Di nuovo, sono perfetti? No. Ma bisogna pensare alla realt√†. Si pu√≤ scrivere il piano perfetto con le macrocalorie calcolate al secondo decimale, un'enorme variet√† di verdure e 12 ore di esercizio fisico dedicate a tutti i diversi gruppi muscolari, ma un piano √® solo un piano, non esiste. La vera questione √® come si interagisce con esso, e se non si riesce a mantenere il piano per pi√π di 3 giorni, non √® affatto un piano. Questi pasti sono deliziosi, facili, sazianti, economici, disponibili praticamente in qualsiasi negozio, durano per giorni in frigorifero e richiedono meno tempo rispetto all'ordinare cibo da asporto. Avere queste opzioni senza vincoli significa che √® probabile che le si integri in un cambiamento di stile di vita sostenibile, invece di andare a caccia della perfezione assoluta.

A questo proposito; molte persone con disturbi alimentari ascoltano podcast su salute e benessere. Forse consiglierei di smettere, tendono ad alimentare il panico e a enfatizzare gli effetti negativi di alimenti relativamente innocui. Anche questo pu√≤ portare a catastrofizzare anche la pi√π piccola delle "imperfezioni", come mangiare una "barretta proteica ultra processata" o bere una bibita analcolica senza zucchero. Ho sostituito i miei podcast sulla "salute" con altri incentrati sugli hobby che mi piacciono, ed √® stato molto meglio.

Mi sono sbarazzata della bilancia, non mi peso da circa un anno. Il peso oscilla molto ogni giorno, e con queste oscillazioni ho davvero lottato. Se mi limitavo pesantemente e mi svegliavo pi√π pesante, rinunciavo immediatamente. Mi limitavo anche molto, eccitata all'idea di quanto potessi perdere in un giorno. Liberarmene ha cambiato immediatamente la mia mentalit√†, passando da una prospettiva giornaliera a una a lungo termine. Ogni tanto scatto foto dei "progressi" e i miei parametri di salute vengono monitorati dal mio Apple Watch, ma non mi impegno molto in nessuna misurazione.

In termini di attivit√†, il mio cambiamento di stile di vita √® avvenuto nell'arco di 3 anni: ho iniziato ad arrampicare indoor 1-2 volte a settimana, poi ho gradualmente costruito un gruppo di amici appassionati di arrampicata con cui amo trascorrere il tempo, il mio amore per l'arrampicata indoor si √® poi trasformato in quello per l'arrampicata outdoor, il che ha significato che ho iniziato ad allenarmi per l'escursionismo, il che mi ha dato la forma fisica necessaria per dedicarmi all'arrampicata alpina. Do la priorit√† a questi hobby e li pratico ogni volta che ho un po' di tempo libero, perch√© li adoro e la mia vita √® costruita attorno a loro. Invece di andare a mangiare/bere con gli amici, andiamo ad arrampicare. Se abbiamo tutti un giorno libero, andiamo a fare un'escursione. Se sincronizziamo le settimane di ferie, andiamo in montagna. So che la maggior parte delle persone ha orari meno flessibili dei miei, e i bambini e altre cose complicano enormemente le cose, ma se riesci a trovare una forma di esercizio che ami veramente, che sia BJJ, corsa, roller derby, skateboard, surf, yoga ecc. e costruisci la tua struttura sociale attorn...

de-DE.title: Mumbo-Update 2025
de-DE.description:
Heute gebe ich euch allen ein Update dar√ºber, was 2025, drei Jahre nach meinem YouTube-Aus, mit mir los ist. Ich spreche √ºber die 10. Staffel von ‚ÄûHermitcraft‚Äú, meine Pl√§ne f√ºr die 11. Staffel, meinen YouTube-R√ºckzug und meine Probleme mit Essst√∂rungen.

Ich bin kein Experte; ich w√ºrde dringend empfehlen, professionellen Rat von Therapeuten einzuholen, die auf Essst√∂rungen spezialisiert sind, wenn ihr ernsthaft damit zu k√§mpfen habt.

Mein erster Ratschlag ist, die Ver√§nderung eures Lebensstils langfristig zu betrachten, anstatt euch auf schnelle L√∂sungen zu konzentrieren. Ich habe mich selbst auf diese unhaltbaren, restriktiven Di√§ten gesetzt, mir gesagt, dass ich fast t√§glich unglaublich intensiv trainieren muss, und innerhalb einer Woche war ich ersch√∂pft, unmotiviert und fiel unweigerlich vom Weg ab ‚Äì dann habe ich mich selbst daf√ºr ge√§rgert, dass ich ‚Äûschon wieder versagt‚Äú habe, und mich mit extremen Essattacken getr√∂stet.

Was mir wirklich geholfen hat, sind 3-4 unglaublich schnelle Rezepte, die ich selbst kochen kann. Ich rede von weniger als 5 Minuten. Sind sie der absolut ges√ºndeste Goldstandard f√ºr Vollwertkost? Nein. Aber ein perfektes Standardrezept, das einen Gang zum Supermarkt und 30 Minuten Zubereitungszeit erfordert, bedeutet, dass ich, sobald ich unter Zeitdruck stehe, abends eine Pizza Hut mit dreifacher K√§semischung esse.

Einige Beispiele f√ºr diese superschnellen Gerichte:

- Mikrowellen-Burrito mit Bohnenmischung, Mikrowellen-Chili ohne Fleisch, Tofu, Brokkoli und Feta. Alles in einer Pfanne zubereitet. √úber 80 g Eiwei√ü, jede Menge Ballaststoffe. Maximal 5 Minuten.
- Ein Topf mit kalten Nudeln (Tomaten und Kr√§utern), Tofu und Feta. Alles in einer Pfanne, nur um es zu erhitzen, vielleicht 3 Minuten? Ich mische die Nudeln auch mit Pesto/Chili, um Abwechslung zu schaffen.
- Pfannengerichte. Eine Art Nudelpackung mit Gew√ºrzen, eine Pfannengem√ºsemischung und Tofu. Vielleicht 5 Minuten?
- Falafeln und Couscous, vielleicht etwas Hummus und Pitabrot.

Und nochmal: Sind sie perfekt? Nein. Aber man muss die Realit√§t ber√ºcksichtigen. Man kann den perfekten Plan mit bis auf die zweite Dezimalstelle berechneten Makrokalorien, einer riesigen Gem√ºseauswahl und 12 Stunden Training f√ºr alle Muskelgruppen aufstellen, aber ein Plan ist nur ein Plan, er existiert nicht. Entscheidend ist, wie man damit umgeht, und wenn man ihn nicht l√§nger als drei Tage durchh√§lt, ist er eigentlich gar kein Plan. Diese Gerichte sind lecker, einfach, s√§ttigend, g√ºnstig, in praktisch jedem Gesch√§ft erh√§ltlich, halten sich tagelang im K√ºhlschrank und sind schneller zubereitet als Essen zum Mitnehmen. Mit diesen stressfreien Optionen integriert man sie wahrscheinlich in eine nachhaltige Lebensstil√§nderung, anstatt nach absoluter Perfektion zu streben.

In diesem Sinne: Viele Menschen mit Essst√∂rungen h√∂ren Gesundheits- und Wellness-Podcasts. Ich w√ºrde vielleicht empfehlen, damit aufzuh√∂ren, denn sie neigen dazu, Angst zu sch√ºren und die negativen Auswirkungen relativ harmloser Lebensmittel zu √ºbertreiben. Das wiederum kann dazu f√ºhren, dass man selbst kleinste Unvollkommenheiten wie den Verzehr eines hochverarbeiteten Proteinriegels oder eine zuckerfreie Limonade als Katastrophe auffasst. Ich habe meine Gesundheits-Podcasts gegen solche √ºber Hobbys ausgetauscht, die mir Spa√ü machen, und das war viel besser.

Ich habe meine Waage entsorgt und mich seit etwa einem Jahr nicht mehr gewogen. Das Gewicht schwankt t√§glich stark, und diese Schwankungen haben mir wirklich zugesetzt. Wenn ich mich stark einschr√§nkte und schwerer aufwachte, gab ich sofort auf. Ich schr√§nkte mich auch extrem stark ein, weil ich begeistert war, wie viel ich an einem Tag abnehmen k√∂nnte. Durch den Verzicht habe ich meine Denkweise sofort von einem t√§glichen auf einen langfristigen Zeitplan umgestellt. Ich mache zwar ab und zu wieder Fotos von meinem Fortschritt, und meine Gesundheitsdaten werden von meiner Apple Watch erfasst, aber ich messe nicht wirklich viel.

Was meine Aktivit√§ten angeht, hat sich mein Lebensstil √ºber einen Zeitraum von drei Jahren ge√§ndert: Ich begann 1-2 Mal pro Woche mit dem Hallenklettern, baute dann langsam rund ums Klettern einen Freundeskreis auf, mit dem ich gerne Zeit verbringe, meine Liebe zum Hallenklettern wuchs sich dann zu einer Liebe zum Klettern im Freien aus, was wiederum bedeutete, dass ich mit dem Wandern begann, was mir die Fitness f√ºr das Bergklettern gab. Diese Hobbys haben f√ºr mich oberste Priorit√§t und ich gehe ihnen nach, wann immer ich Freizeit habe, weil ich sie liebe und mein Leben sich darum dreht. Anstatt mit Freunden essen/trinken zu gehen, gehen wir klettern. Wenn wir alle einen freien Tag haben, gehen wir wandern. Wenn wir uns freie Wochen teilen, machen wir einen Ausflug in die Berge. Ich wei√ü, die meisten Leute haben weniger flexible Zeitpl√§ne als ich, und Kinder usw. machen die Dinge ungemein kompliziert, aber wenn Sie eine Sportart finden, die Sie wirklich lieben ‚Äì sei es BJJ, Laufen, Roller Derby...

snippet.title: Exclusive: Wife speaks after husband sucked into MRI machine dies, says he was 'snatched' | News 12
snippet.description:
A Nassau County woman is recalling the harrowing experience of her husband being pulled into an MRI machine by the metal chain around his neck. Keith McAllister was critically injured when he was pulled into the machine and later died from his injuries, according to Nassau County police. It happened Wednesday afternoon at Nassau Open MRI in Westbury on Long Island. Adrienne Jones-McAllister says she saw her husband walk toward the table and saw the machine "snatch him."

it.title: Esclusiva: la moglie racconta la morte del marito risucchiato nella macchina per la risonanza mag...
it.description:
Una donna della contea di Nassau ricorda la straziante esperienza di suo marito trascinato dentro una macchina per la risonanza magnetica per la catena di metallo che gli pendeva dal collo. Keith McAllister √® rimasto gravemente ferito quando √® stato trascinato dentro la macchina ed √® poi morto per le ferite riportate, secondo la polizia della contea di Nassau. L'incidente √® avvenuto mercoled√¨ pomeriggio al Nassau Open MRI di Westbury, a Long Island. Adrienne Jones-McAllister racconta di aver visto suo marito dirigersi verso il tavolo operatorio e di aver visto la macchina "rapirlo".

snippet.title: Gyokeres? We need MORE PLAYERS | Mikel Arteta | Arsenal in Asia
snippet.description:
Arsenal manager Mikel Arteta updates progress on the club's pursuit of Viktor Gyokeres and other transfer targets on the first day of their pre-season tour of Singapore.

TIMESTAMPS
0:00 INTRO
0:05 excited about new season after great training with new signings in Spain. Adapting to weather and unable to train this morning
0:45 new signings like 'shaking the tree' and bring new energy - heights need to go to a new level
1:10 players are convinced how good they are and ready to take the next step.
1:58 Zubimendi? a long process and he could have gone elsewhere but he wanted to come to Arsenal and we are all so impressed now we have seen him in training.
2:49 Gyokeres? Can't comment on player who is not part of our group yet
3:10 four signings already - can we expect more players to sign and come to Singapore? Still a long time to go and we are still short on numbers
3:40 Who can get into first team from young players? Whoever knocks down the door - up to them
4:08 Partey charges reaction? club has been clear that legal matters mean I can not comments
4:40 confident club followed right processes? 100 per cent 
4:57 Calafiori expectations for his second season?  his injuries last season were on international duty with Italy and now we want him consistently available.
6:01 changes since you played in Singapore with Arsenal ten years ago? our supporters here are v passionate and we want to connect with them.
7:11 ten years ago I did not expect to be sitting here (as manager) 
7:50 four players in still hopes we can improve the team
8:33 I am pleased with where we are so far in the transfer window and hopeful there will be more very soon
8:52 window has been exciting as seen ambition club has throughout the club
9:11 Gabriel be fit for new season? He is committed and has a new contract and played 45 minutes against Watford at weekend and looks in good shape 
10:02 Madueke - why so many Chelsea players? They have a lot of great players and we focus on who we want rather than the club they are in. he is having a break aftyer winning the Club World Cup and the players who know him are delighted we have signed him. 
  

@HaytersTV ‚Äì Football Up Close. Visit our website: https://hayters.com/
 
We go behind the scenes with the biggest names in football to bring you interviews, training, news, live coverage, fans‚Äô voices and funniest moments. If you love football, you‚Äôll love Hayters TV. Subscribe now!

snippet.title: We Went To Canada To See The U.S. Product Boycotts ‚Äî And What We Found Was Striking
snippet.description:
In response to U.S. tariffs and President Trump's policies, 71% of Canadian consumers are shifting away from American products, with the "Buy Canada" movement. CNBC traveled to Canada to speak with locals and meet with a grocery store owner to find out the impact of the boycotts. As the U.S. economy is projected to lose up to $90 billion in 2025 due to shifting consumer sentiment. The fallout is global with Mexico and countries in the European Union joining. And it extends to tourism, with Canadian visits to the U.S. down 50%, crippling U.S. border economies.

snippet.title: will.i.am + Taboo - EAST LA (Official Music Video)
snippet.description:
will.i.am + Taboo - East LA (Official Music Video)

We are Los Angeles. We are Angelenos. We are Americans. Some of us born here, some of us migrated here. We are a great country and our borders should be protected. You would think that the idea of border control would make residents feel safe - but it's pumped fear into our communities. 

They're going after people that make our city beautiful. People who put food in our supermarkets, take care of other people's kids, work two to three jobs so they can take care of their families. It breaks my heart. 

I wanted to make this video to change the vibe and celebrate the folks that make our cities great. The very same people who are being disregarded, dehumanized, and demoralized. 

Thank you for your contributions. Thank you for your work. We will get through this. 

Production Company: Clash of The Artistic Minds
Executive Producer: Sterling Hampton IV
Directors: will.i.am & Sterling Hampton IV

Colorist: Kinan Chabani

Management: Polo Molina

snippet.title: Tron: Ares | Official Trailer
snippet.description:
Watch the brand-new trailer for Tron: Ares and experience it in theaters, filmed for IMAX, October 10.
 
Tron: Ares follows a highly sophisticated Program, Ares, who is sent from the digital world into the real world on a dangerous mission, marking humankind‚Äôs first encounter with A.I. beings. The feature film is directed by Joachim R√∏nning and stars Jared Leto, Greta Lee, Evan Peters, Hasan Minhaj, Jodie Turner-Smith, Arturo Castro, Cameron Monaghan, with Gillian Anderson, and Jeff Bridges. Sean Bailey, Jeffrey Silver, Justin Springer, Jared Leto, Emma Ludbrook and Steven Lisberger are the producers, with Russell Allen serving as executive producer.

Grammy¬Æ-award winning rock band Nine Inch Nails composed the score for ‚ÄúTron: Ares,‚Äù and today, the band dropped "As Alive As You Need Me To Be" ‚Äîthe soundtrack album‚Äôs first single and the first official music from the band in five years. Listen to "As Alive As You Need Me To Be‚Äù and view the visualizer: https://nineinchnails.lnk.to/AAAYNMTB. The track is featured in the new trailer for ‚ÄúTron: Ares.‚Äù
 
‚ÄúTron: Ares (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack),‚Äù featuring all original music by Nine Inch Nails, will be released on September 19 via Interscope Records. The release marks the first-ever film score by the pioneering band, although bandmates Trent Reznor and Atticus Ross have composed 20 scores under their own names, winning two Oscars¬Æ, three Golden Globes¬Æ, a GRAMMY¬Æ and an Emmy¬Æ in the process.

en.title: Tron: Ares | Official Trailer
en.description:
Watch the brand-new trailer for Tron: Ares and experience it in theaters, filmed for IMAX, October 10.
 
Tron: Ares follows a highly sophisticated Program, Ares, who is sent from the digital world into the real world on a dangerous mission, marking humankind‚Äôs first encounter with A.I. beings. The feature film is directed by Joachim R√∏nning and stars Jared Leto, Greta Lee, Evan Peters, Hasan Minhaj, Jodie Turner-Smith, Arturo Castro, Cameron Monaghan, with Gillian Anderson, and Jeff Bridges. Sean Bailey, Jeffrey Silver, Justin Springer, Jared Leto, Emma Ludbrook and Steven Lisberger are the producers, with Russell Allen serving as executive producer.

Grammy¬Æ-award winning rock band Nine Inch Nails composed the score for ‚ÄúTron: Ares,‚Äù and today, the band dropped "As Alive As You Need Me To Be" ‚Äîthe soundtrack album‚Äôs first single and the first official music from the band in five years. Listen to "As Alive As You Need Me To Be‚Äù and view the visualizer: https://nineinchnails.lnk.to/AAAYNMTB. The track is featured in the new trailer for ‚ÄúTron: Ares.‚Äù
 
‚ÄúTron: Ares (Original Motion Picture Soundtrack),‚Äù featuring all original music by Nine Inch Nails, will be released on September 19 via Interscope Records. The release marks the first-ever film score by the pioneering band, although bandmates Trent Reznor and Atticus Ross have composed 20 scores under their own names, winning two Oscars¬Æ, three Golden Globes¬Æ, a GRAMMY¬Æ and an Emmy¬Æ in the process.

snippet.title: Past Life #2 - Remember This?
snippet.description:
Past Life is an odd mix of a Social and PvP Minecraft game started by Grian. Players are thrown into a tiny world with almost no rules, except survive as long as possible.

In Past Life, we will be playing through the older versions of Minecraft and updating to a newer one each episode.

3+ Lives = Green Player
2 Lives = Yellow Player
1 Life = Red Player

Red Players are given the goal of killing all the other players in the game. Yellow Players can kill Green Players.

The final battle is looming ‚Äî and with it, a darkness more powerful and more deadly than anything they‚Äôve faced before. To end this nightmare, they‚Äôll need everyone ‚Äî the full party ‚Äî standing together, one last time.

snippet.title: Watch live: SpaceX Falcon 9 rocket launches 24 Starlink satellites to polar orbit from California
snippet.description:
Watch live coverage as SpaceX launches a Falcon 9 rocket carrying 24 of its Starlink V2 Mini satellite into a polar orbit. Liftoff of the Starlink 17-3 mission from pad 4E at Vandenberg Space Force Base is scheduled for Friday, July 18, at 8:52 p.m. PDT / 11:52 p.m. EDT (0352 UTC on Saturday, July 19). The first-stage booster, tail number B1082, making its 14th flight, will land on the drone ship 'Of Course I Still Love You' about eight and a half minutes after launching.

Our live coverage with commentary will begin about 30 minutes before launch.

Videos like this are made possible by the support of our members. Join this channel to get access to perks:

snippet.title: Mortal Kombat 2 - Official 'Uncaged Fury' Teaser Trailer (2025) Karl Urban
snippet.description:
Don't miss the 'Uncaged Fury' Teaser Trailer for Mortal Kombat 2, the upcoming action film based on the hit Mortal Kombat game IP distributed by Warner Bros. Pictures. Take a look at the in-universe film trailer for Uncaged Fury starring the one and only Johnny Cage, portrayed by Karl Urban. 

Uncaged Fury sees the legendary Johnny Cage take on a band of goons with ease, making use of pipes, fast-paced combat skills, and an aura unlike any other.

Mortal Kombat 2 is in theaters on October 24.
